forfeits the advantage} (6. Bb3 $5 $14) 6... Nf6 $4 {Black threatens to win
material: Nf6xe4. gives the opponent counterplay} (6... Qa5+ $142 {Black
clearly has the better chances} 7. Nc3 Bxf3 8. Qxf3 Qxg5 $19) 7. Nc3 (7. Nbd2
Qb6 $11) 7... O-O (7... Qa5 $5 {must be considered} 8. Bxf6 Bxf6 $15) 8. h3 $11
Bxf3 {Black forks: d1, g2+e4} 9. Qxf3 Nbd7 {Black has a cramped position} 10.
O-O-O (10. O-O c5 11. Be3 Nh5 $11) 10... a5 (10... b5 11. Bb3 Qc7 12. Qe3 $11)
11. a3 (11. e5 Ne8 12. Rhe1 d5 13. Nxd5 cxd5 14. Qxd5 Nb6 15. Qxd8 Rxd8 16.
