Nxb5 Qb6 19. Ra7 Bb7 20. Bd2 d5 21. Ba5 Qc6 22. e5 Ne4 23. b4 Rfe8 24. Nxd4 Qc3
25. Nb5 Qc6 26. Qa1 Bh4 27. Re2 Bxf2+ {Sinurat,T (2249)-Sukandar,I (2363)
Jakarta 2013 0-1 (45)}) 13... h6 {Covers g5} 14. Bd3 {White has an active
position} Bd7 15. b4 {White threatens to win material: b4xa5} Nc4 {[%cal Yb6a4,
Yc4b6,Ya5c4] Manoeuvre Na5-c4-b6-a4} 16. Qe2 Rfc8 17. Nbd2 (17. a4 Nh5 $11)
17... Nb6 (17... a5 $5 $15) 18. Nb3 $11 Na4 {The black knight on an outpost}
19. a3 Qd8 20. Bd2 Rc7 21. Rac1 Rac8 22. Rxc7 Rxc7 23. Rc1 Rxc1+ 24. Bxc1 Nh7 {
White has an active position} 25. Qc2 Ng5 26. Nxg5 Bxg5 27. Bxg5 hxg5 28. Be2
f6 29. Bd1 Qc8 30. Qd3 (30. Qxc8+ Bxc8 31. Kf1 Nb2 $11) 30... Qc3 {Black
threatens to win material: Qc3xd3} 31. Qe2 (31. Qxc3 Nxc3 32. Bc2 Be8 $11)
31... Nb6 (31... Nb2 $142 $17) 32. Qh5 $4 {releasing the pressure on the
opponent} (32. Qd2 Na4 $11) 32... Qc8 $4 {Loses material. there were better
ways to keep up the pressure} (32... Qe1+ $142 {Black missed this excellent
chance} 33. Kh2 Qxe4 $19) 33. Na5 $11 Nc4 (33... Qc1 34. Nb3 Qxa3 35. Bg4 Qxb3
36. Be6+ Bxe6 37. Qe8+ Kh7 38. Qh5+ Kg8 39. Qe8+ Kh7 40. Qh5+ Kg8 $11) 34. Nxc4
(34. Nc6 $5 Qe8 35. Qxe8+ Bxe8 36. Bg4 $11) 34... bxc4 $11 {Black has a new
passed pawn: c4} 35. Qe2 c3 {White has to watch this pawn} 36. Bc2 {Blocks the
pawn on c3} Bb5 {Black threatens to win material: Bb5xe2} 37. Qd1 Qc4 38. Qh5
$4 (38. a4 $142 {would hold out} Be8 39. Qb1 $11) 38... Qf1+ $19 39. Kh2 Qxf2
40. a4 (40. Qd1 g4 $1 {Deflection: c2} 41. Qxg4 Qxc2 42. Qe6+ Kh8 $19) 40...
Bd7 (40... Be2 $142 {and Black has prevailed} 41. Qe8+ Kh7 $19) 41. Qd1 Qf4+ (
41... Bxh3 $142 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} 42. Qf3 Qxf3 43. gxf3 $19) 42.
Kh1 g4 43. Qd3 $4 {terrible, but what else could White do to save the game?} (
43. hxg4 Kf7 44. Qe1 $17) 43... gxh3 (43... g3 44. Qf3 Qd2 45. Qd1 $19) 44.
gxh3 (44. Bb3 $19 {is no salvation}) 44... Qd2 (44... Bxh3 $142 {and Black can
celebrate victory} 45. Bd1 Qh4 46. Qxc3 Bg4+ 47. Kg2 Bxd1 48. Qc8+ Kh7 $19) 45.
b5 $4 {solves nothing} (45. Qxd2 $142 cxd2 46. Kg2 $17) 45... axb5 (45... Qxd3
$142 {and Black can already relax} 46. Bxd3 axb5 $19) 46. axb5 $4 {the final
mistake, not that it matters anymore.} (46. Qxd2 cxd2 47. a5 Bxh3 48. a6 $19)
46... Qxd3 47. Bxd3 c2 (47... Bxb5 $142 {and the rest is a matter of technique}
48. Bc2 f5 $19) 48. Bxc2 Bxb5 49. Kg2 Kh7 50. Kg3 $2 (50. Kf3 g6 $19) 50... Kh6
51. Bd1 $4 {shortens the misery for White} (51. h4 $19) 51... g6 52. Kh4 (52.
Kf2 {otherwise it's curtains at once} f5 53. Bc2 $19) 52... Bd3 53. Bf3 (53.
Ba4 {does not win a prize} Bxe4 54. Kg3 Bxd5 $19) 53... f5 54. exf5 gxf5 55.
Kg3 e4 56. Bd1 Bc4 (56... Kg5 $142 $19 {secures victory}) 57. Kf4 $17 Kg6 58.
h4 $4 {another bit of territory lost} (58. Ba4 $142 $17) 58... Bxd5 $19 59. h5+
(59. Be2 {hardly improves anything} Be6 $19) 59... Kf6 60. h6 Bg8 61. Bh5 (61.
Ba4 {doesn't change the outcome of the game} Bh7 $19) 61... Bh7 62. Be8 d5 63.
