{D11: Slav Defence: 3 Nf3 sidelines and 3...Nf6 4 e3 Bg4} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3.
Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 a6 5. b3 b5 6. c5 $146 {White gets more space} (6. Bd3 Bg4 7. Ba3
(7. Nbd2 e6 (7... Nbd7 8. Bb2 e6 9. Qc2 Bh5 10. O-O Be7 11. Rac1 O-O 12. Ne5
Qc8 13. cxb5 cxb5 14. Bxh7+ Nxh7 15. Qxc8 Rfxc8 16. Nxd7 Bb4 17. Nf3 Bxf3 18.
gxf3 Nf8 19. Nxf8 Kxf8 20. Rxc8+ Rxc8 21. Rc1 Rxc1+ 22. Bxc1 {Fayard,A (2360)
-Huerga Leache,M (2440) Pamplona 2007 1/2-1/2 (32)}) 8. O-O Nbd7 9. h3 Bh5 10.
e4 dxc4 11. bxc4 Nc5 {1/2-1/2 (11) Kocic,S (2260)-Jelic,G (2210) Belgrade 2007}
) 7... Bxf3 8. gxf3 g6 9. O-O Bg7 10. f4 O-O 11. Nd2 Nbd7 12. Nf3 Re8 13. Qe1
Qc8 14. Qe2 c5 15. cxd5 Nxd5 16. Rac1 b4 17. Bb2 Qb7 18. Ne5 cxd4 19. Bxd4 Nxe5
20. fxe5 e6 {Franic,M (2426)-Sedlak,N (2524) Pula 2003 0-1 (35)}) (6. Ne5 Nfd7
7. Nd3 e6 8. Nd2 Bd6 9. Bb2 O-O 10. g3 a5 11. Bg2 bxc4 12. bxc4 Ba6 13. Qc2 Nf6
14. O-O Nbd7 15. e4 dxe4 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 Qc7 18. Rfe1 Rab8 19. Bxh7+ Kh8
20. Be4 c5 {Inarkiev,E (2664)-Sychev,K (2425) St Petersburg 2015 1-0}) 6... g6
7. Be2 Nbd7 8. O-O Bg7 9. Bb2 a5 10. Qc2 O-O 11. Nbd2 Re8 12. a3 e6 13. b4 a4 {
This push gains space} 14. Rfe1 Ra7 15. Bf1 h6 {Prevents intrusion on g5} 16.
e4 dxe4 17. Ne5 {White threatens to win material: Ne5xc6} Rc7 18. Nxe4 Nxe4 19.
Rxe4 Nf6 {Black threatens to win material: Nf6xe4} 20. Re2 Ree7 21. g3 Bd7 22.
Bg2 Be8 23. h4 h5 24. f3 {Covers e4+g4} (24. Rae1 Nd5 $16) 24... Nd5 {A
comfortable square for the black knight} 25. f4 Kh7 26. Rf1 {Black has a
cramped position} f6 {Black threatens to win material: f6xe5} 27. Nd3 Bf7 {
Black has a cramped position} 28. Bh3 Re8 29. g4 (29. Rfe1 $5 $14 {might be a
viable alternative}) 29... hxg4 $15 30. Bxg4 f5 {Black threatens to win
material: f5xg4} 31. Bf3 {White has an active position} Kg8 32. Rh2 {White has
a very active position} (32. Qd2 Qxh4 33. Bxd5 exd5 $11) 32... Ne3 $15 {
[%cal Rd8d4,Rg7d4,Gb2d4] Attacks the backward pawn on d4. Black threatens to
win material: Ne3xc2. Black forks: c2+f1} 33. Qf2 Nxf1 34. Kxf1 {Black wins
the exchange} Ree7 35. Ne5 {White threatens to win material: Ne5xc6} (35. h5
Be8 $11) 35... Be8 $15 36. Qg2 $2 {[%cal Re5g6,Rg2g6,Ge8g6] Attacking the
backward pawn on g6} (36. Qe2 $142 $15 {would allow White to play on}) 36...
Bxe5 $19 37. fxe5 Rg7 (37... Rh7 38. h5 $17) 38. Qf2 Rh7 (38... g5 $142 $5 39.
hxg5 Qxg5 $17) 39. Bc1 $11 Rcd7 {Black threatens to win material: Rd7xd4} 40.
Be3 (40. Bg5 $142 {and White has air to breath} Qc7 41. Rg2 $11) 40... f4 $1
$17 {Deflection: d4} 41. Bxf4 Rxd4 42. Bg5 Qd7 43. Bxc6 $4 {causes even
greater problems} (43. Qc2 $142 $17) 43... Rd1+ (43... Rd1+ 44. Kg2 Qxc6+ 45.
Kg3 Rd3+ 46. Kg4 Qe4+ 47. Qf4 Qe1 48. Rh3 Qe2+ 49. Rf3 Rf7 50. Bf6 Bc6 51. Kg5
Rxf3 52. Qg4 Rf5+ 53. Qxf5 Qh5+ 54. Kf4 Qf3+ 55. Kg5 Qxf5+ 56. Kh6 Rh7#) 0-1

