{C55: Two Knights: 4 d3, 4 d4 exd4 5 e5 and Max Lange Attack} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. Bc4 Be7 4. d3 Nf6 5. Nc3 O-O 6. h3 $146 {Controls g4} (6. Bg5 d6 7. Qd2
(7. h3 Na5 8. Bb3 Bd7 9. Qd2 c6 10. Ne2 d5 11. Ng3 Qc7 12. O-O Rfe8 13. Nh4
Rad8 14. Qe2 h6 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Nhf5 Kh7 17. Qh5 Be6 18. c3 Nxb3 19. axb3 Bg5
20. Qf3 dxe4 21. Nxe4 Bf4 {Scurhan,G (2158)-Pessi,E (2225) Sovata 2001 0-1 (47)
}) 7... Bg4 8. Be3 Bxf3 9. gxf3 Nd4 10. Bxd4 exd4 11. Ne2 d5 12. Bb3 c5 13. e5
Nd7 14. f4 Nb6 15. c3 dxc3 16. bxc3 d4 17. cxd4 cxd4 18. f5 Nd5 19. Kf1 Bb4 20.
Qb2 Bc3 {Kaplan,J (2455)-Biyiasas,P (2420) Sao Paulo 1973 1-0 (45)}) (6. a3 d6
7. h3 Nd4 (7... Be6 8. O-O Qd7 9. Bxe6 fxe6 10. Re1 Kh8 11. d4 exd4 12. Nxd4 e5
13. Nf3 Rae8 14. Be3 Bd8 15. Nh2 Qf7 16. Rf1 Re6 17. Qd3 Qg6 18. Rad1 Nh5 19.
Qb5 {1/2-1/2 (19) Roos,D (2355)-Flear,G (2480) France 1987}) (7... a6 8. Ne2 d5
9. exd5 Nxd5 10. b4 Be6 11. Bb2 Bd6 12. Ba2 Re8 13. c4 Nf4 14. Nxf4 exf4 15.
O-O Bf5 16. Qd2 Bg6 17. c5 Bf8 18. Qxf4 Re2 19. Be5 Rc8 20. Bc4 Be7 21. Rfe1
Rxe1+ 22. Rxe1 {Haas,C (2230)-Castagna,R (2265) Zuerich 1989 1-0}) 8. Be3 Nxf3+
9. Qxf3 Be6 10. g4 c6 11. Bxe6 fxe6 12. Qg3 Nd7 13. g5 d5 14. Ne2 Bd6 15. Qg4
Qe7 16. h4 b5 17. Kf1 Bc5 18. Rh3 Qf7 19. Qg3 Bxe3 20. Qxe3 d4 {Morozevich,A 
(2545)-Georgiev,K (2660) Tilburg 1993 0-1 (105)}) 6... b6 7. Be3 Bb4 8. O-O
Bxc3 9. bxc3 {White has the pair of bishops} Bb7 10. Re1 h6 {Consolidates g5}
11. Nh4 Ne7 (11... Na5 12. Bb3 $11) 12. Qd2 (12. Qf3 d5 13. exd5 Qd6 $14) 12...
Kh7 $11 13. f3 {Covers g4} d5 {Black threatens to win material: d5xc4} 14. Bb3
c5 15. exd5 {White has a new passed pawn: d5} Nfxd5 {White's piece can't move:
h4} 16. Bf2 g5 {Black threatens to win material: g5xh4.} 17. Rxe5 gxh4 18. Rh5
{White has a mate threat} (18. d4 Qc7 19. Bxd5 Nxd5 $11) 18... Ng8 (18... Qd6
19. Re1 $11) 19. Bxh4 (19. d4 $5 $11 {should be investigated more closely})
19... Qd6 $15 20. Qg5 (20. Re1 $15) 20... Rfd8 $4 {a transit from better to
worse} (20... Nxc3 $142 {and Black could have gained the advantage} 21. Re1 Qg6
$19) 21. Bxd5 {White forks: f7+b7} Qxd5 22. Qg4 Qe6 (22... Qd6 23. Bxd8 Rxd8
24. Qf5+ Kg7 25. Qe5+ Qxe5 26. Rxe5 $11) 23. Bxd8 Qxg4 24. hxg4 Rxd8 {White
has new doubled pawns: g2+g4. Black has a new backward pawn: h6} 25. Re1 Bd5
26. c4 Be6 27. Ree5 (27. Kf2 Kg6 $16) 27... Nf6 {Black threatens to win
material: Nf6xh5} 28. Rh4 Kg6 29. Kf2 Rd4 30. Kg3 a5 (30... Bd7 31. Rh1 $14)
31. f4 Kg7 $2 (31... Bd7 $142 $16) 32. g5 $18 hxg5 33. Rxg5+ (33. fxg5 $142 $5
Nd7 34. Rxd4 Nxe5 35. Rd6 $18) 33... Kf8 $16 34. Rh8+ Ke7 35. Rb8 Nh7 $2 (35...
Rd6 36. Kf3 $16) 36. Rh5 $4 {White is ruining his position} (36. Re5 $142 {
makes sure everything is clear} Nf8 37. Rxb6 $18) 36... Nf6 $16 37. Rg5 {
Twofold repetition} Rd6 (37... Nh7 38. Re5 Nf6 39. Rxb6 Nd7 $18) 38. Re5 $4 {
hands over the advantage to the opponent} (38. Kf3 $142 $16) 38... Kd7 $4 {
lets it slip away} (38... Nd7 $142 {with excellent chances for Black} 39. Rb7
Kd8 $19) 39. f5 $18 Bxf5 (39... Kc7 {cannot undo what has already been done}
40. Rf8 Nd7 41. fxe6 fxe6 42. Rf7 $18) 40. Rxf5 Ke6 41. Rf1 Nh5+ (41... a4 {
cannot change destiny} 42. Kh4 $18) 42. Kh4 Ng7 (42... Nf6 {doesn't improve
anything} 43. g4 Kd7 44. g5 $18) 43. g4 Ke7 (43... Ke5 {there is nothing
better in the position} 44. Rxf7 Ne6 $18) 44. Rb7+ Ke6 (44... Ke8 {cannot
change what is in store for ?} 45. Rfxf7 Ne6 46. Rf6 $18) 45. Rbxf7 (45. Rfxf7
Ke5 46. Rxg7 Rc6 $18) 45... Ne8 46. g5 (46. Rb7 $142 {makes it even easier for
White} Rd7 47. Re1+ Kd6 48. Rxb6+ Kc7 49. Rb5 $18) 46... Ke5 (46... Rd8 {
hoping against hope} 47. Rf8 Kd7 48. R1f7+ Ke6 $18) 47. Re7+ Kd4 48. Rxe8 Kc3
49. Re2 Kb2 50. a4 Ka3 51. Rf6 (51. Rf6 Rd4+ 52. Kh5 $18) 1-0

